{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase threshold for car tax surcharge to cars with a list price of \u00a345,000",
        "additional_details": "As it stands if you purchase a new car with a retail price of \u00a340,000 or more you will be subject to \u00a3390 a year EXTRA road tax bringing it to over \u00a3500 a year for some people.\r\n \r\nConsidering inflation being the way that it is, many family size cars are now into and over the \u00a340000 bracket for even some of the more basic models. Especially if you want to purchase a hybrid vehicle to \u201chelp the planet\u201d you are likely to be going over the \u00a340000 margin meaning an extra \u00a332.50 per month.\r\n",
        "background": "We ask the government to raise the threshold for the additional \u00a3390 tax from cars with a list price of \u00a340000 to those with a list price of \u00a345000. Many households needing to buy new family sized cars will already be stretching to pay the cost, let alone an extra \u00a332.50 a month.",
